WEBVTT

00:01.951 --> 00:03.285
♪ ♪

00:03.286 --> 00:04.786
(sighs)

00:04.787 --> 00:06.253
Hi.

00:06.255 --> 00:08.757
Did you have
a good day, darling?

00:08.758 --> 00:09.724
No, I did not.

00:09.725 --> 00:11.927
It is a free-for-all out there.

00:11.928 --> 00:14.596
The homeless are brawling
with the runaways.

00:14.597 --> 00:17.332
The pickpockets are
fighting with the jaywalkers.

00:17.333 --> 00:20.734
Even the hookers are surly,
and they're paid to be nice.

00:21.771 --> 00:23.571
You know what that is?

00:23.572 --> 00:26.006
Mercury is in retrograde.

00:27.810 --> 00:30.277
What the hell does that mean?

00:30.279 --> 00:31.579
You're gonna have to ask Joyce.

00:31.580 --> 00:34.581
All I know is I can't touch her
till the new moon.

00:35.818 --> 00:37.585
Well, thanks for the heads up.

00:37.586 --> 00:38.520
What's for dinner?

00:38.521 --> 00:39.587
Gals have been out all day.

00:39.588 --> 00:40.956
You're on your own.

00:40.957 --> 00:42.257
Again?!
Yep.

00:42.258 --> 00:45.059
I went with a handful of peanuts
and a can of beets.

00:46.629 --> 00:47.796
Remind me of that tomorrow

00:47.797 --> 00:50.531
if you hear me
freaking out in the bathroom.

00:51.334 --> 00:52.734
You know, I never said a word

00:52.735 --> 00:54.935
when Molly was writing her book
and I had to fend for myself.

00:54.937 --> 00:57.105
Like an animal.
Like an <i> animal!</i>

00:57.106 --> 00:59.474
But I can't remember the last
time she's written anything.

00:59.475 --> 01:01.943
Keeps saying she's gotta
recharge her batteries.

01:01.944 --> 01:03.345
I'm starting
to think that's code for:

01:03.346 --> 01:04.846
"You're on your own, chump."

01:04.846 --> 01:08.550
What code? That's literally what
Joyce said to me on her way out.

01:08.551 --> 01:10.184
(Molly and Joyce
and Victoria laughing)

01:10.186 --> 01:12.187
I don't believe you!
Hey, honey.

01:12.188 --> 01:14.356
Ah, look who's back.

01:14.357 --> 01:15.323
I'm glad you're here.

01:15.324 --> 01:16.825
What would be the coolest thing

01:16.826 --> 01:18.693
for the Flynn girls
to come home with?

01:18.694 --> 01:19.761
Dinner.

01:19.762 --> 01:20.828
MOLLY: Nope!

01:20.830 --> 01:23.031
♪ Ta-da! ♪

01:23.032 --> 01:24.566
(laughing)

01:24.567 --> 01:25.700
Where did that come from?

01:25.701 --> 01:27.002
34th and Flynn.

01:27.003 --> 01:28.870
Now it's just 34th.

01:28.871 --> 01:30.104
(laughing)

01:31.707 --> 01:33.475
Ah, I'm glad you guys
had a good time

01:33.476 --> 01:35.610
vandalizing the city
that I work all day to protect.

01:35.611 --> 01:37.879
We did. Thank you
for your service.

01:37.880 --> 01:39.113
(chuckling)

01:40.549 --> 01:41.950
Did you get any writing done?

01:41.951 --> 01:43.785
As a matter of fact, no.

01:43.786 --> 01:47.756
I tried, I failed, I drank,
but tomorrow's another day,

01:47.757 --> 01:48.823
or the day after that.

01:48.824 --> 01:51.191
You can't really rush
these things.

01:51.994 --> 01:54.129
Can't you?

01:54.130 --> 01:55.397
What?

01:55.398 --> 01:57.399
Well, if you hit another wall
with your writing tomorrow,

01:57.400 --> 01:59.267
maybe, instead of
running around town

01:59.268 --> 02:02.169
with the good time girls,
you could, I don't know,

02:02.171 --> 02:04.305
put a hot meal on the table
for your husband,

02:04.306 --> 02:06.040
when he gets home.

02:08.244 --> 02:12.079
Did you actually say what
I think you just said?

02:15.418 --> 02:17.918
I did.

02:17.920 --> 02:21.122
Do you have any idea
how insulting that is?

02:21.123 --> 02:22.524
All right, it came out wrong,

02:22.525 --> 02:24.359
but don't listen to my words,
listen to what I'm saying.

02:24.360 --> 02:25.160
What are you saying?

02:25.161 --> 02:27.895
I'm hungry!

02:27.897 --> 02:30.532
So you want your little woman
to hop to in the kitchen.

02:30.533 --> 02:32.700
Look, it has nothing to do with
the fact that she's a woman.

02:32.701 --> 02:36.704
If I was married to a man,
I'd expect the same thing.

02:36.705 --> 02:38.640
Ah! If I were married to a man,

02:38.641 --> 02:41.342
I'd expect that he could survive
one night on his own.

02:41.343 --> 02:43.144
It's been more than one night.

02:43.145 --> 02:44.279
Poor thing!

02:44.280 --> 02:45.946
Look at you withering away.

02:48.217 --> 02:50.084
Again, that's not
what I'm saying.

02:50.086 --> 02:51.553
Well, then, what are you saying?

02:51.554 --> 02:53.253
Yeah!
Yeah.

02:56.559 --> 02:58.159
Vince, help me out here.

02:58.160 --> 02:59.160
I'm not part of this.

02:59.161 --> 03:03.530
I had a handful of peanuts
for dinner, and I'm very happy.

03:06.368 --> 03:09.170
♪ La, la-ba-dee-da ♪

03:09.171 --> 03:12.107
♪ La, la-ba-dee-da ♪

