03:45.909 --> 03:47.975
Everything okay over there?

03:47.977 --> 03:49.778
(grunts) I'm fine.

03:49.779 --> 03:50.811
You're not fine.

03:50.813 --> 03:52.480
You been picking at
your pants all day.

03:54.083 --> 03:58.619
What is it, jock itch?
Ringworm? Chapped crack?

03:59.789 --> 04:02.257
Molly didn't get a chance
to get the laundry done,

04:02.258 --> 04:04.926
so I am wearing
a swimsuit for underwear.

04:05.795 --> 04:07.762
You told me you didn't
own a swimsuit.

04:07.764 --> 04:10.831
I am not going to the water park
with you, Carl!

04:11.901 --> 04:13.969
She's at home all day,
doing nothing,

04:13.970 --> 04:17.103
and I gotta go to work with
my testicles in a net.

04:17.106 --> 04:19.140
You-you-you can't do laundry?

04:19.142 --> 04:21.610
Do you see a washer or dryer
in the squad car?

04:21.611 --> 04:23.744
She's at home, she should do it.

04:23.746 --> 04:24.813
Yeah, say that too loud,

04:24.814 --> 04:26.381
and those testicles
will be out of the net

04:26.382 --> 04:29.083
and dangling from
her rearview mirror.

04:29.085 --> 04:30.452
That's not what I meant.

04:30.453 --> 04:32.887
Wh-When did everybody
get so touchy?

04:32.889 --> 04:35.691
Uh, late '60s, early '70s.

04:35.692 --> 04:37.592
The war of the sexes
is over, baby.

04:37.594 --> 04:39.060
SAMUEL: Yeah, he's right.

04:39.062 --> 04:40.796
All men have left now
are higher wages,

04:40.797 --> 04:42.231
a monopoly on
running corporations,

04:42.232 --> 04:45.199
and control of women's
reproductive rights.

04:45.201 --> 04:47.069
This is not a man-woman thing.

04:47.070 --> 04:49.171
This is
a husband-wife thing, okay?

04:49.172 --> 04:51.240
When Molly was writing
her book with my mom,

04:51.241 --> 04:52.441
I was a team player.

04:52.442 --> 04:54.408
I happily threw
a load of wash in.

04:54.410 --> 04:56.612
Happily?
Hey, I wasn't Mary Poppins,

04:56.613 --> 04:58.680
but I got it done.

04:58.681 --> 05:00.481
But she hasn't written
anything in over two weeks.

05:00.483 --> 05:03.150
At what point
do I get to say something?

05:03.152 --> 05:04.853
You? Never.

05:04.854 --> 05:06.321
Not because you don't
have a point,

05:06.322 --> 05:07.656
but because you lack
the vocabulary

05:07.657 --> 05:09.490
to say it in a tactful way.

05:09.492 --> 05:10.892
Eh, it's a very sensitive issue,

05:10.893 --> 05:13.694
and you're about as delicate
as a rhino on roller skates.

05:14.964 --> 05:16.665
Yeah, I was picturing a bear
on a beach ball, but...

05:16.666 --> 05:17.866
I think we saying
the same thing.

05:17.867 --> 05:19.033
SAMUEL: Yeah, yeah.

05:19.869 --> 05:20.968
Oh!

05:20.970 --> 05:24.105
One of my barnacles
is tangled in the net.

05:26.242 --> 05:28.976
♪ ♪

05:29.979 --> 05:31.546
How's the writing going?

05:31.547 --> 05:34.382
So far, all I've written
is three pages of S's.

05:34.384 --> 05:36.150
I fell asleep on the keyboard.

05:36.953 --> 05:39.420
Is the story about a snake?

05:41.324 --> 05:43.558
Yeah. You know what
the sequel's called?

05:43.559 --> 05:44.725
Shhh...

05:46.696 --> 05:49.530
Sweetie, maybe you need
a little break from the writing.

05:49.532 --> 05:50.699
You know, get some fresh air

05:50.700 --> 05:52.300
in that cigar bar up the street.

05:53.703 --> 05:54.903
You can bring your laptop.

05:54.904 --> 05:57.271
Maybe you'll pass out
and write another story.

05:57.273 --> 06:00.574
No! Do not do this to me again.

06:00.576 --> 06:02.611
What? Is it so wrong
for a mother

06:02.612 --> 06:04.845
to want to spend happy hour
with her two daughters?

06:04.847 --> 06:06.914
Every day? Yes.

06:08.184 --> 06:11.252
Uh, even if I wanted to, I got
all this laundry to do.

06:11.254 --> 06:13.721
If you do that,
you're saying Mike's right.

06:13.723 --> 06:15.824
Well, if I don't do that,
I gotta keep wearing

06:15.825 --> 06:17.591
these bike shorts for underwear!

06:19.128 --> 06:20.829
Look, if all you're
worried about is laundry,

06:20.830 --> 06:22.297
we can do that, no problem,

06:22.298 --> 06:24.498
and still enjoy
mother-daughter mudslides.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.803
We can?

06:27.804 --> 06:29.003
Absolutely!

06:29.005 --> 06:31.940
I got a system for getting it
done quickly and painlessly.

06:31.941 --> 06:33.407
Vince!

06:34.544 --> 06:37.244
What, i-is there a new moon?

06:38.848 --> 06:41.015
♪ ♪

06:41.017 --> 06:43.484
Hey, I'm home!

06:47.890 --> 06:51.727
Wow! Somebody has been
working on her creases!

06:51.728 --> 06:53.694
Thanks for noticing.

06:55.064 --> 06:57.132
Hope you don't mind,
I went with a Swedish cuff.

06:57.133 --> 06:58.667
Very versatile...
with one simple flip,

06:58.668 --> 07:02.137
it can take you from the couch
to the conference room.

07:02.138 --> 07:03.372
Where's Molly?

07:03.373 --> 07:05.673
Ah, she went out for drinks
with Joyce and Victoria.

07:05.675 --> 07:07.408
And she pawned
the laundry off on you?

07:07.410 --> 07:09.444
Are you kidding?
I love doing this.

07:09.445 --> 07:11.413
Ironing is very Zen.

07:11.414 --> 07:14.216
The wrinkles are your problem,
the iron is your solution

07:14.217 --> 07:17.051
and your hand is...
well, well, your hand.

07:18.020 --> 07:19.421
You know what this is?

07:19.422 --> 07:22.823
This is a deliberate
"screw you," from Molly, to me.

07:22.825 --> 07:24.458
I'm sensing a lot
of anger from you.

07:24.460 --> 07:26.427
Trust your senses.

07:26.429 --> 07:30.331
Boy, if anyone needs
to iron, it's you.

07:31.634 --> 07:34.469
Five minutes in,
your blood pressure drops,

07:34.470 --> 07:37.272
your heart rate slows, huh?

07:37.273 --> 07:39.874
Come on...
take a vacation.

07:41.277 --> 07:44.044
You really want to put
that in my hand right now?

07:44.046 --> 07:45.747
Suit yourself.

07:45.748 --> 07:47.915
See ya on the other side.

07:50.353 --> 07:52.319
Om...

07:55.224 --> 07:57.492
(inhales deeply)

07:57.493 --> 07:59.326
Om...

08:00.997 --> 08:03.097
♪ ♪

08:05.301 --> 08:06.600
(sighs)

08:10.339 --> 08:11.505
(groans)

08:13.142 --> 08:15.176
Mm-mm, not good.

08:16.212 --> 08:18.680
(Molly, Joyce and Victoria
talking and laughing)

08:18.681 --> 08:19.681
MOLLY: Hey!

08:19.682 --> 08:21.716
Aloha!

08:21.717 --> 08:23.751
Oh! What's that stench?

08:23.753 --> 08:24.820
It's my dinner.

08:24.821 --> 08:27.221
Lentils, the saddest
of the soups.

08:28.524 --> 08:30.458
I hope you guys had fun!
JOYCE: Oh!

08:30.460 --> 08:32.092
We had a blast!

08:32.094 --> 08:36.431
Molly won a trivia contest,
I came in third in the limbo,

08:36.432 --> 08:40.302
and Victoria placed first
in the wet coconut bra contest.

08:40.303 --> 08:42.037
I can't take all the credit.

08:42.038 --> 08:44.004
They did most of the work.

08:44.807 --> 08:46.241
And I'm eating a can of crap

08:46.242 --> 08:47.843
that's been here
since I moved in.

08:47.844 --> 08:50.277
Guess we're all winners tonight!

08:51.147 --> 08:53.248
Well, no one's forcing you
to eat old soup.

08:53.249 --> 08:55.116
There's always
peanuts and beets.

08:55.117 --> 08:56.650
(all laughing)

08:58.120 --> 09:00.187
Did you do anything
productive today?

09:00.189 --> 09:03.457
I guess you didn't see
that the laundry got done.

09:03.459 --> 09:05.560
Oh, yeah.
I saw Vince did a real nice job

09:05.561 --> 09:07.027
with what you were
supposed to do.

09:07.029 --> 09:09.463
What I was <i> supposed</i> to do?

09:09.465 --> 09:10.499
(gasps)

09:10.500 --> 09:12.166
All right, Coconuts,
that's our cue.

09:12.168 --> 09:13.335
Good, 'cause the fumes

09:13.336 --> 09:15.970
from that Porta Potti soup
are getting to me.

09:15.972 --> 09:18.707
Hey, that stink is my dinner!

09:18.708 --> 09:20.442
That I had to make myself.

09:20.443 --> 09:21.676
Oh, I'm sorry.

09:21.677 --> 09:23.545
I didn't realize that my job
was to cook you dinner

09:23.546 --> 09:24.979
and be the perfect little wife.

09:24.981 --> 09:28.516
Well, if it was your job,
you'd probably be fired.

09:28.518 --> 09:29.584
What?

09:29.585 --> 09:30.918
You heard me.

09:30.920 --> 09:34.989
I'm taking my sad,
stinky soup to-go.

09:34.991 --> 09:36.457
(snorts)

09:55.083 --> 09:57.216
(brightly): Good morning.

09:59.754 --> 10:01.687
What's going on?

10:01.689 --> 10:03.457
Breakfast in bed
for the king of the castle.

10:03.458 --> 10:04.657
(giggles)

10:05.927 --> 10:08.395
Coffee, eggs over medium,
fresh-squeezed juice...

10:08.396 --> 10:10.396
and I removed the pulp
with a strainer,

10:10.398 --> 10:13.500
because your perfect little wife
knows how angry you get

10:13.501 --> 10:15.367
when things aren't just so.

10:17.438 --> 10:19.105
All right, what'd you do to it?

10:19.107 --> 10:21.841
Spit in the orange juice,
wipe the toast on the floor?

10:21.843 --> 10:25.611
Nonsense. Why would I ever
do such a thing, husband?

10:26.414 --> 10:28.481
Knock it off.

10:28.483 --> 10:31.517
Have I done something
to displease you, husband?

10:31.519 --> 10:33.319
Quit calling me husband...
it's creepy.

10:34.255 --> 10:35.921
Do you prefer master?

10:35.923 --> 10:37.357
All right, okay.

10:37.358 --> 10:38.925
I see what you're doing.

10:38.926 --> 10:40.326
You're trying
to make me feel guilty

10:40.328 --> 10:41.861
for what I said last night.

10:41.863 --> 10:43.029
If you say so.

10:43.030 --> 10:44.897
The man is always right.

10:47.735 --> 10:50.035
But here's something you didn't
factor in to your little plan.

10:50.037 --> 10:51.438
Probably not.
Yeah.

10:51.439 --> 10:52.739
I'm hungry.

10:52.740 --> 10:53.874
And guess what?

10:53.875 --> 10:55.207
I don't feel bad!

10:55.209 --> 10:58.111
I feel good that there's
a breakfast in front of me.

10:58.112 --> 10:59.912
How's that make you feel?

10:59.914 --> 11:01.448
Well, how do I know how I feel

11:01.449 --> 11:04.416
if you haven't told me
how I feel?

11:04.418 --> 11:06.385
(giggles) Fine.

11:06.387 --> 11:08.588
If that is the way
you want to play it,

11:08.589 --> 11:10.157
let the games begin.

11:10.158 --> 11:12.325
Mmm, cinnamon toast.

11:12.326 --> 11:14.961
Mmm, you probably buttered this
with your shoe,

11:14.962 --> 11:16.530
but it's going down sweet.

11:16.531 --> 11:17.597
(laughs)

11:17.598 --> 11:19.166
You're smart.

11:19.167 --> 11:22.168
I'm glad you're enjoying it.

11:23.204 --> 11:25.338
And just know
that when you're finished,

11:25.339 --> 11:27.406
I'll be here ready to make love.

11:29.944 --> 11:31.945
Well, that sounds good to me.

11:31.946 --> 11:33.380
And just like this breakfast,

11:33.381 --> 11:37.082
if you don't think I'm gonna
enjoy it, you are wrong.

11:41.656 --> 11:43.789
Be with you in a minute.

11:49.697 --> 11:51.998
So what did Stepford Molly
pack you for lunch?

11:51.999 --> 11:53.266
(chuckles)

11:53.267 --> 11:55.001
Shaved roast beef on a hoagie,

11:55.002 --> 11:56.770
Mmm.
Fuji apples...

11:56.771 --> 11:58.405
sliced and skinned... ooh.

11:58.406 --> 12:00.940
Plus, Rice Krispie Treat.

12:00.942 --> 12:02.241
Did she use Fruity Pebbles?

12:02.243 --> 12:04.543
She yabb-dabba-did.

12:04.545 --> 12:06.947
And this somehow is supposed
to make you miserable?

12:06.948 --> 12:08.715
Uh, this is a mind game
she's playing.

12:08.716 --> 12:12.518
Unfortunately for her,
this mind don't play it.

12:12.520 --> 12:15.487
So you're gonna outsmart her
by undersmarting her.

12:15.489 --> 12:17.490
Pretty smart, huh?

12:17.491 --> 12:18.558
You-you did it.

12:18.559 --> 12:19.893
I mean, you finally broke
that wild horse.

12:19.894 --> 12:21.260
You got everything you wanted.

12:21.262 --> 12:22.729
Yeah.

12:22.730 --> 12:24.363
(chuckles)

12:29.804 --> 12:31.171
Is something wrong with it?

12:31.172 --> 12:32.372
(sighs softly)

12:32.373 --> 12:33.640
I don't know how she did it.

12:33.641 --> 12:34.674
What?

12:34.675 --> 12:36.877
This is a loveless sandwich.

12:36.878 --> 12:39.546
It tastes of spite
in every bite.

12:39.547 --> 12:41.448
Well, now you're just
being picky.

12:41.449 --> 12:44.551
Do you want food and sex
or do you want love?

12:44.552 --> 12:45.718
Oh.

12:46.554 --> 12:47.654
Ah.

12:47.655 --> 12:49.889
"Have an amazing day, husband."

12:50.691 --> 12:52.492
Wow.

12:52.493 --> 12:54.159
She hates me.

12:59.667 --> 13:01.534
Hey, w-what are you doing
on the couch?

13:01.535 --> 13:04.670
Shouldn't you be packing
Mike's pipe with poison tobacco?

13:06.173 --> 13:07.407
No, I'm done with all that.

13:07.408 --> 13:08.707
Mike saw right through me.

13:08.709 --> 13:10.911
Turns out giving him all
the food and sex he wanted

13:10.912 --> 13:12.712
didn't upset him.

13:12.713 --> 13:15.547
Played me like
a cheap carnival game.

13:16.350 --> 13:17.717
Yeah, I know how you feel.

13:17.718 --> 13:20.986
I once lost six games
of tic-tac-toe to a chicken.

13:22.189 --> 13:24.524
It's not exactly the same Th...

13:24.525 --> 13:27.359
Well, yeah,
it's exactly the same thing.

13:28.162 --> 13:29.863
Hey, you mind if
I set up shop here?

13:29.864 --> 13:32.098
Or is that gonna mess
with your writing mojo?

13:32.099 --> 13:35.267
No, I'm just writing
a stupid snake story.

13:36.003 --> 13:37.803
All I got right now is dialogue.

13:39.040 --> 13:41.942
Well, you know what might help
with your creative constipation?

13:41.943 --> 13:44.977
A little iron in your diet.

13:45.947 --> 13:47.480
Come on, Vince, cut the act.

13:47.481 --> 13:49.214
No one likes ironing.

13:49.216 --> 13:50.583
If you say so.

13:50.584 --> 13:52.785
(humming)

13:58.392 --> 14:00.025
Do you really enjoy that?

14:00.027 --> 14:01.227
I sure do.

14:01.228 --> 14:02.996
And you know what the icing
on the cake is?

14:02.997 --> 14:05.165
The look on your mother's face
when she opens her closet

14:05.166 --> 14:07.434
and sees rows
of freshly-pressed blouses,

14:07.435 --> 14:10.669
pants and age-inappropriate
halter tops.

14:12.273 --> 14:15.407
So you and Botox are the reason
she has no wrinkles.

14:16.544 --> 14:17.944
The man behind the woman.

14:17.945 --> 14:19.913
And when I need my hair dyed,

14:19.914 --> 14:21.648
she's the woman behind the man.

14:21.649 --> 14:24.284
We each pitch in
where we need to.

14:24.285 --> 14:28.855
Yeah, you try not to keep
score, but you always do.

14:28.856 --> 14:32.091
Right now, I'm way in front.

14:41.202 --> 14:43.168
Mikey, what a surprise!

14:43.170 --> 14:45.171
Hungry or you need my toilet?

14:45.172 --> 14:46.306
(chuckles)

14:46.307 --> 14:49.142
Can't a son just come
by and check up on his mother?

14:49.143 --> 14:50.643
Sit down.

14:50.644 --> 14:51.945
I'll warm up
some lasagna for you.

14:51.946 --> 14:53.246
Oh, you don't have to do that.

14:53.247 --> 14:54.581
Corner piece if you got it.

14:54.582 --> 14:55.715
Yeah.

14:55.716 --> 14:57.217
I know my boy.

14:57.218 --> 14:58.618
Yeah, you do.

14:58.619 --> 15:00.220
Can I get you a beer?

15:00.221 --> 15:01.388
Yeah, that'd be nice.

15:01.389 --> 15:03.490
A cold beer after
a long day at work.

15:03.491 --> 15:05.358
Yeah, here you go.

15:05.359 --> 15:07.394
See? How hard is this?

15:07.395 --> 15:08.795
What are you talking about?

15:08.796 --> 15:09.763
Nothing.

15:09.764 --> 15:11.031
I just appreciate the effort.

15:11.032 --> 15:14.167
I'm happy someone's happy
to make me happy.

15:14.168 --> 15:15.268
Of course.

15:15.269 --> 15:16.469
You work hard.

15:16.470 --> 15:19.272
You deserve a beer
and a hot meal.

15:19.273 --> 15:22.675
Careful who you say that around.

15:22.676 --> 15:23.943
Who, your wife?

15:23.944 --> 15:25.345
What, she thinks she's too good

15:25.346 --> 15:27.279
to crack open a beer for my boy?

15:27.281 --> 15:29.848
It's not that she thinks
she's too good to...

15:29.850 --> 15:31.418
Let me tell you something.

15:31.419 --> 15:35.387
Waiting on you should be
the biggest pleasure of her day.

15:35.389 --> 15:37.322
That's a little much.

15:37.324 --> 15:38.925
Nothing's too much for you.

15:38.926 --> 15:43.395
Boy, I tell you, I'd spoil you
rotten if we were married.

15:45.900 --> 15:49.368
You know what, Mom, I'm-I'm
not as hungry as I thought.

15:49.370 --> 15:51.470
In fact, my stomach just turned.

15:52.673 --> 15:53.772
Really?

15:53.774 --> 15:55.041
You don't want anything?

15:55.042 --> 15:58.343
Be more than happy
to run a hot bath for you.

15:59.146 --> 16:02.015
No, no, uh, like I said,
I just came in here

16:02.016 --> 16:03.316
to check on you and...

16:03.317 --> 16:05.718
(chuckles)
I should really run...

16:05.719 --> 16:07.820
very, very far away.

16:09.290 --> 16:14.393
That girl will never appreciate
how much I do for her.

16:18.566 --> 16:19.833
Mol, you out here?

16:19.834 --> 16:21.700
Under the car.

16:21.702 --> 16:23.469
Why?

16:24.405 --> 16:26.638
You're not cutting
my brake lines, are you?

16:26.640 --> 16:28.574
No.

16:28.576 --> 16:30.209
Although I could.

16:31.479 --> 16:34.546
There are online courses that'll
teach you just about anything.

16:36.951 --> 16:38.718
Just to be clear,
you didn't, right?

16:38.719 --> 16:40.253
No.

16:40.254 --> 16:43.823
Though I did change your oil
and swap out your filter

16:43.824 --> 16:45.125
and top off all your fluids.

16:45.126 --> 16:47.025
Molly, you didn't have
to do that.

16:47.027 --> 16:49.329
I mean, it's totally
cool that you did.

16:49.330 --> 16:51.363
But you didn't have to.

16:51.365 --> 16:53.032
I know. I wanted to.

16:53.033 --> 16:55.001
I felt like pitching in,

16:55.002 --> 16:57.604
and I know car stuff is not
the most obvious choice,

16:57.605 --> 17:00.272
but hey, Vince likes ironing.

17:00.274 --> 17:01.975
Well, I gotta say,

17:01.976 --> 17:05.010
you're a lot cuter
than the guy at Valvoline.

17:05.012 --> 17:06.012
Cheaper, too.

17:06.012 --> 17:07.713
I work for dinner.

17:07.714 --> 17:10.983
Well, have you tried
my famous stinky lentil soup?

17:10.984 --> 17:12.885
I have.

17:14.088 --> 17:15.555
Then we should go out.

17:15.556 --> 17:17.189
Yeah, we should.

17:19.160 --> 17:20.959
I'll get my coat.

17:22.762 --> 17:25.231
I am gonna see
if I can figure out

17:25.232 --> 17:27.398
where all these extra parts go.

17:29.103 --> 17:31.003
Or not.

17:41.853 --> 17:43.086
Hey.
Hey.

17:43.087 --> 17:44.988
Look at you.

17:44.989 --> 17:46.255
Writing again.

17:46.257 --> 17:48.225
Kind of.
I'm on a mechanics' forum.

17:48.226 --> 17:49.993
Apparently some of the parts
I threw away

17:49.994 --> 17:51.761
were pretty important.

17:51.762 --> 17:54.498
I wouldn't drive the car over 40

17:54.499 --> 17:56.700
till I get this figured out.

17:56.701 --> 17:58.068
My little Pep Girl.

17:58.069 --> 18:00.036
(sniffs)
Hey, is that dinner I smell?

18:00.037 --> 18:01.104
It is.

18:01.105 --> 18:02.172
You're amazing.

18:02.173 --> 18:04.574
I made a pork loin.

18:04.575 --> 18:06.142
You take off that shirt.

18:06.143 --> 18:08.111
I'm not wasting two hours
and a can of Shout

18:08.112 --> 18:10.679
wrestling pig juice out of that.

18:12.183 --> 18:13.683
Say what you want,

18:13.684 --> 18:16.086
but my mother hit the jackpot
when she married that one.

18:16.087 --> 18:17.987
(chuckles) We all did.

18:19.757 --> 18:21.492
Think he knows anything
about cars?

